The paper discusses improving the intellectual effectiveness of individual AI systems through learning in heterogeneous multiagent systems and mathematical approaches for non-iterative corrections of errors. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as the primary sub-categories. The use of multiagent systems also suggests a potential fit with the multiagent systems sub-category (cs.MA). The paper also discusses stochastic separation theorems, which are related to neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
